      out.write("&lt;style type=&#8221;text/css&#8221;&gt; <em><span >@import url(<em><span>Path To stylesheet.css</span></em>)</span></em> &lt;/style&gt;<br />\n");
      out.write("&lt;/head&gt;<br />\n");
      out.write("&lt;body&gt;</p>\n");
      out.write("<p>By using an external style sheet, all of your (X)HTML files link to one CSS file in order to style the pages. This means, that if you need to alter the design of all your pages, you only need to edit one .css file to make global changes to your entire website.</p>\n");
      out.write("<p>Here are a few reasons this is better.</p>\n");
